          <head xml:lang="eng">Seal</head>
          <ab><lb n="1"/>vāraka-maṇḍala-viṣayādhika<lb n="2"/>raṇasya<!-- 
Pargiter does not edit the seal inscription, noting only that just a few characters are legible, but what remains is consistent with the seal of %IN00130. There are facsimiles of the seals in IA39 (next ot p208), but my scan is poor, so even for %IN00130 I cannot be sure where the line break is. I can see dhi near the end of the first line, but I cannot tell if there is a ka next to it or just some noise. In the second line only sya is discernible; raṇa can be seen with some imagination; there is probably no ka here. The legend would probably be quite legible in the hardcopy. 
--></ab>
        </div>
        <div n="B" type="textpart">
          <head xml:lang="eng">Plates</head>
