No mangala symbol is reported at the beginning of this inscription. The scanned facsimile is useless. 
-->
          <!-- 
In l3-4 Pargiter reads ku at the end of l3, but thinks the reading is in fact kr̥, and he believes the intended word was kriyāmātya. Sircar keeps ku and conjectures kumārāmātya.. 
-->
          <!-- 
For vyāpāraṇḍya in l3, Pargiter offers the interpretation "one who manages trade" while Sircar believes the reading may be vāpāra-kāraṇḍya, for -kāraṇḍīya, "in charge of boxes [of documents]". See also note to %IN00129/5. 
-->
          <!-- 
In l5-6 Pargiter prints (svāmi)nā .. ṣṭha (vya)vaharatā and says the ṣṭha may perhaps be sya and the reading should probably be tasya; he then corrects to vyavaharato. I adopt his conjecture, but Sircar goes down a different path, reading (svāmī) then supplying [+| yato], and reading sya as asya and also correcting to vyavaharato. Pargiter's edition shows the nā of svāminā as clear, while Sircar ignores it altogether. Nothing is visible in my scan. 
-->
          <!-- 
In l6-7 Partiger notes that the last two characters should be maha, but "so much as appears on the plate hardly agrees therewith". Still, ttara in l7 practically requires maha. Sircar emends viṣaya to vinaya, apparently taking vinayakuṇḍa as a name. 
-->
          <p><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->I</supplied><unclear>ccheyaṁ</unclear> bhava<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->tāṁ pras</supplied><unclear>ādād</unclear> <gap quantity="2" reason="illegible" unit="character"/> <unclear cert="low">mahā-ko</unclear><lb break="no" n="11"/>ṭṭika-<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->nā</supplied>ma <gap precision="low" quantity="10" reason="illegible" unit="character"/> <unclear cert="low">pa</unclear> <gap quantity="2" reason="illegible" unit="character"/> <unclear cert="low">tta</unclear> <supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->bhava</supplied><unclear cert="low">dbhyo</unclear> kṣettra-kulya<lb break="no" n="12"/>-vāpaikaṁ yathā<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->rghe</supplied>no<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->pakkrī</supplied>ya mā<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->tā-pi</supplied>ttro<unclear>r ā</unclear><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->tmanaś ca</supplied> puṇyābhivr̥ddhaye <unclear>gu</unclear><lb break="no" n="13"/>ṇavanta-k<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->ā</supplied>ṇ<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->v</supplied>a-<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->vāji</supplied>sin<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->e</supplied>ya-<unclear>lau</unclear><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->hittya</supplied>-<unclear>bha</unclear>ṭṭa-go<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->mi</supplied>datta-svāmi<supplied reason="omitted">ne</supplied> pra<lb break="no" n="14"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->ti</supplied>pā<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->dituṁ</supplied><supplied reason="subaudible">.</supplied> ta<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->d a</supplied>rha<unclear>tha</unclear> <supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->bha</supplied>radvāj<unclear>a</unclear>-sagottr<supplied cert="low" reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->ā</supplied> <supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->bha</supplied>vanto smatto mūlyam ādā<lb break="no" n="15"/>ya <gap quantity="4" reason="illegible" unit="character"/> <choice>
              <unclear>dh</unclear>
              <unclear>p</unclear>
